---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
const updated = '2026-06-18';
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`Privacy policy | ${SITE.name}`}
  description="How Aheadcount handles personal data: no tracking cookies, demo runs in your browser, minimal data collection."
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container-x prose prose-slate max-w-3xl">
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
      <p><em>Last updated: {updated}</em></p>

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE.name} is an independent prototype operated from {SITE.controllerLocation}. The operator of {SITE.name}
        is the data controller under the GDPR. You can reach us at <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Beta sign-ups:</strong> your email, optional business/industry, and the segment/intent of your interest, plus referrer and UTM parameters for source analysis.</li>
        <li><strong>The planner demo:</strong> nothing. Everything you type into the demo is computed in your browser and never sent to us.</li>
        <li><strong>Site analytics:</strong> aggregated, pseudonymized visit statistics via Cloudflare Web Analytics. No cookies, no personally identifiable IP storage.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Why we process it</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To tell you when the beta opens (basis: consent).</li>
        <li>To learn which industries and tiers are most wanted (basis: legitimate interest).</li>
        <li>To answer your questions (basis: legitimate interest / pre-contract).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. How long we keep it</h2>
      <p>Emails are kept until you unsubscribe or up to 24 months after your last interaction. Analytics are aggregated and kept for at most 24 months.</p>

      <h2>5. Who we share it with</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Formspree</strong> (form processing) — under a data processing agreement.</li>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> — cookieless visit statistics; no personal data passed.</li>
        <li><strong>GitHub Pages</strong> (GitHub Inc.) — static hosting of this site.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We never sell or rent personal data. Ever.</p>

      <h2>6. Your rights (GDPR)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Access, rectification and erasure (unsubscribe).</li>
        <li>Restriction and objection.</li>
        <li>Data portability.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a> to exercise a right. We respond within 30 days.</p>

      <h2>7. Security</h2>
      <p>Static hosting over TLS (HTTPS) on all traffic. No customer business data is stored on our servers — the planner runs entirely in your browser.</p>

      <h2>8. Changes</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy. We'll email signed-up users about significant changes.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
